{"lemma":"سَمَر","slug":"سَمَر","root":"س.م.ر","root_slug":"س-م-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/س-م-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20671","n20675","n20676"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to keep watch, preserve, to stay awake, to speak at night, to speak late at night, to live night-life, to be around at night (of people and animals)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become brown"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to brown, to add brownness to, to tan etc."},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a female given name, Samar"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"acacia, a plant of several species of the Acacieae tribe","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fasten by means of nails, to tack etc."},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to nail"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine plural of أَسْمَر (ʔasmar)","tags":["form-of","masculine","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew שמר (šamár, “to guard, save, keep watch”).\n\nDenominal verb of مِسْمَار (mismār).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20671","headword_ar":"سَمَرَ","root":"smr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samorN","text_ar":"سَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwrN","text_ar":"سُمُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He held a conversation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse, by night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he waked; continued awake; did not sleep:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asmr","text_ar":"اسمر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"may signify the same; or may be of the same class as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ahozala","text_ar":"اَهْزَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomana","text_ar":"اَسْمَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and thus signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came to have, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samar","text_ar":"سَمَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conversation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse, by night"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) [See also 3.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samarati AlmaA$iyapu","text_ar":"سَمَرَتِ المَاشِيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumuwrN","text_ar":"سُمُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cattle pastured by night without a pastor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed themselves by night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) [or simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pastured by night;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a A_ibilanaA tasomuru","text_ar":"اـِنَّ اـِبِلَنَا تَسْمُرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily our camels pasture by night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samarati AlA_ibilu layolatahaA kul~ahaA","text_ar":"سَمَرَتِ الاـِبِلُ لَيْلَتَهَا كُلَّهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels pastured during their night, the whole of it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samarati AlmaA$iyapu Aln~abaAta","text_ar":"سَمَرَتِ المَاشِيَةُ النَّبَاتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cattle pastured upon the herbage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) aor. as above: (M:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pastured upon the herbage by night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as one says,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samara Alxamora","text_ar":"سَمَرَ الخَمْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drank mine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAtuwA yasomuruwna","text_ar":"بَاتُوا يَسْمُرُونَ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1425},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxamora","text_ar":"الخَمْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They passed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spent, their night drinking wine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiyrN","text_ar":"سَمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samura","text_ar":"سَمُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samira","text_ar":"سَمِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, in a copy of the M"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samara","text_ar":"سَمَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; inf. n. of each"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumorapN","text_ar":"سُمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsmAr~","text_ar":"اسمارّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisomiyraArN","text_ar":"اِسْمِيرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tawny, brownish, dusky,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dark in complexion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"colour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the colour termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumorap","text_ar":"سُمْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. below]. (S, M, Msb, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smarahu","text_ar":"سمَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2, first signification. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smara Eayonahu","text_ar":"سمَرَ عَيْنَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samalahaA","text_ar":"سَمَلَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blinded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqaA^a","text_ar":"فَقَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his eye with a heated iron instrument:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sml","text_ar":"سمل"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he put out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blinded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaHala","text_ar":"كَحَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his eye with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misomaAr","text_ar":"مِسْمَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nail"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Mgh, Msb, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of iron"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made hot"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he put out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blinded, his eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqaA^ahaA","text_ar":"فَقَاَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samara All~abana","text_ar":"سَمَرَ اللَّبَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A5-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samara somahu","text_ar":"سَمَرَ سْمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA","Msb","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n20675","headword_ar":"سَمَرٌ","root":"smr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Conversation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse, by night;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musaAmarapN","text_ar":"مُسَامَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A. *) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amaru baEoda AlEi$aA='i","text_ar":"السَّمَرُ بَعْدَ العِشَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, accord. to one relation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amoru","text_ar":"السَّمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Conversation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse by night is after nightfall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^afoEaluhu Als~amara","text_ar":"لَا اَفْعَلُهُ السَّمَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlqamara","text_ar":"وَالقَمَرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do it as long as men hold conversation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse in a night when the moon shines:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as long as men hold conversation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse by night, and as long as the moon rises:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ever."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [See also below. The pl.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomaArN","text_ar":"اَسْمَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is often used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tales related in the night, for amusement:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this usage is probably post-classical.] ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Conversation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse, by day."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place in which people hold conversation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse by night;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which they make,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remain awake;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAmirN","text_ar":"سامِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * M, K;) which latter is expl. by Lth as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place in which people assemble for conversation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse by night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  A people's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assembling and holding conversation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse in the dark."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And hence, (TA,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dark;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"darkness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, M, K, TA.) So in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halafa","text_ar":"حَلَفَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAls~amari waAlqamari","text_ar":"بِالسَّمَرِ وَالقَمَرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He swore by the darkness and the moon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotuhu","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samarFA","text_ar":"سَمَرًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him in the night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A night in which there is no moon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"hence the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^afoEalu *`lika Als~amara waAlqamara","text_ar":"لَا اَفْعَلُ ذٰلِكَ السَّمَرَ وَالقَمَرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do that when the moon does not rise nor when it does rise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr.) [See also above.] ―         -b8-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shade of the moon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b9-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light of the moon; moonlight;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to some, the primary signification; because they used to converse, or discourse, in it. (TA.) ―         -b10-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time of daybreak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Turiqa","text_ar":"طُرِقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawomu samarFA","text_ar":"القَوْمُ سَمَرًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people were come to at daybreak."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M.) ―         -b11-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiyrN","text_ar":"سَمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Lh","M","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n20676","headword_ar":"سَمُرٌ","root":"smr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloHN","text_ar":"طَلْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gum-acacia-tree; acacia,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mimosa, gummifera"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb;) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloH","text_ar":"طَلْح"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having small leaves, short thorns, and a yellow fruit"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baramap","text_ar":"بَرَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which men eat: there is no kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EDAh","text_ar":"عضاه"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"better in wood: it is transported to the towns and villages, and houses are covered with it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its produce is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pod"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubolapN","text_ar":"حُبْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hbl","text_ar":"حبل"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mimosa unguis cati"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Forskål (Flora Aegypt. Arab., pp. cxxiii. and 176:)] n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samurapN","text_ar":"سَمُرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, Mgh, Msb, K:) [in the S,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samurN","text_ar":"سَمُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samurapN","text_ar":"سَمُرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but it is a coll. gen. n.:] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samurapN","text_ar":"سَمُرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samuraAtN","text_ar":"سَمُرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomurN","text_ar":"اَسْمُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a pl. of pauc., of which the dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usayomirN","text_ar":"اُسَيْمِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$obaha $arojN","text_ar":"اَشْبَهَ شَرْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arojFA lawo A^an~a A^usayomirFA","text_ar":"شَرْجًا لَوْ اَنَّ اُسَيْمِرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharj would resemble Sharj if a few gum-acacia-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"were found there: Sharj is a certain valley of El-Yemen: for the origin of this prov., see Freytag's Arab. Prov., i. 662]. (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A^aSoHaAba Als~amurapi","text_ar":"يَا اَصْحَابَ السَّمُرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O people of the gumacacia-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in a saying of the Prophet, was addressed to the persons meant in the Kur xlviii. 18. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","Mgh","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}